description.value: 'Book of the Dead', Papyrus of Nebseny; Scenes of the Afterlife (sheet 18): the vignette shows a schematized landscape known as the Field of Offerings or Field of Reeds. Watercourses are a dominant feature. Nebseny is shown guiding a plow drawn by oxen, while above he is using a sickle to harvest the fully grown crop. Nebseny also appears seated before a table of offerings. He is also shown adoring gods and burning incense, while a divine barque is represented at lower right.

Palimpsest papyrus with demotic text recto and verso. On the recto the beginning of a 'Demotic Name-book' (30 lines), to which EA 10856.3 Fragment B also belongs, as well as P. Carlsberg 425. On the verso are parts of three columns of accounts.

One of the sheets of the roll is at right angles to the rest, so that the fibres on the recto run vertically in one area.

description.value:
Papyrus written with black ink with demotic administrative text on recto (3 ll.), verso pasted down.
Receipt for taxes paid by Teianti(?) daughter of Zeho in respect of land or houses purchased by her.
Thompson's MS Catalogue: "year 5 Athyr 22 of Ptol. Philadelphus = BC. 280. Jan. 21 [...] Perhaps 10536 is the tax receipt in connection with the sale in P. dem. Rylands xii.xiii."
Nos.10522-10532 and 10535-10537 belonging to the same archive, cf. P. BM EA 10522.
